item.value: "Dumb" mode starts and ends in a {@link com.intellij.openapi.application.WriteAction}, so if you're inside a {@link ReadAction} on a background thread, it won't suddenly begin in the middle of your operation. But note that whenever you start a top-level read action on a background thread, you should be prepared to anything being changed, including "dumb" mode being suddenly on and off. To avoid executing a read action in "dumb" mode, please use {@link runReadActionInSmartMode} or {@link com.intellij.openapi.application.NonBlockingReadActioninSmartMode}.
